The win propelled Spain into the quarter-finals, where they will face Germany in a highly anticipated clash.

name: George Russell
summary: In a dramatic turn of events, George Russell of Mercedes emerged victorious in the Austrian Grand Prix after a collision between Max Verstappen of Red Bull and Lando Norris of McLaren. Russell inherited the lead when the frontrunners collided on lap 69, securing his maiden Formula 1 victory. Verstappen and Norris were both forced to retire from the race, while Russell went on to hold off Carlos Sainz Jr. of Ferrari to take the checkered flag. This win marks Mercedes' first victory of the 2023 season and is a significant moment for Russell, who has consistently impressed since joining the team in 2022.
